Chordate:



Chordate decided, while he was waiting, too change all the access codes, then 
the comm. frequencies.  

Typing several commands into the main computer console, blue text appeared:

    Estimated Time Until Codes Are Finished Being Changed: 10 cycles

"Excellent." Chordate said, leaning back in his chair.  Important codes like 
to the cells, armory, and etc. were not stored anywhere inside the main 
database.  That would be just plain militarily stupid!  But, it would be 
stupid not to change the less important codes anyway.
